description:
In e2e_testnet.rs line 533, the final success line is:

    eprintln\!("PASS: txid = {txid}, alice_scan_tip = {alice_scan_tip}");

alice_scan_tip was read at line 353, before the payment was sent. After send_payment() and Bob's scan, Alice's store was never re-scanned, so this variable holds the pre-payment scan height. Printing it here implies it reflects Alice's post-payment state, which it does not. Fix: either drop alice_scan_tip from the success message or re-read alice_store.scan_tip() before the final eprintln.
